(41, 'POST626850', 'eng', 'Toddler', 'The Health Benefits of Water', 'Text', 'Immediate', '2021-04-26 16:48:00', '#toddler', '#toddler', '<p style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\">Did you know that your body weight is approximately 60 percent water? Your body uses water in all its cells, organs, and tissues to help regulate its temperature and maintain other bodily functions. Because your body loses water through breathing, sweating, and digestion, itâ€™s important to rehydrate by drinking fluids and eating foods that contain water. The amount of water you need depends on a variety of factors, including the climate you live in, how physically active you are, and whether youâ€™re experiencing an illness or have any other health problems.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(125, 116, 157);\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">Water Protects Your Tissues, Spinal Cord, and Joints</strong></span></p><p data-spx-slot=\"1\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\">Water does more than just quench your thirst and regulate your bodyâ€™s temperature; it also keeps the tissues in your body moist. You know how it feels when your eyes, nose, or mouth gets dry? Keeping your body hydrated helps it retain optimum levels of moisture in these sensitive areas, as well as in the blood, bones, and the brain. In addition, water helps protect the spinal cord, and it acts as a lubricant and cushion for your joints.</p><div class=\"swoop-container nolinks\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\"><div class=\"spx-adwords-iab spx-ai-content\" data-purpose=\"lp\" data-target=\"http://swoop:/campaign/load?campid=enbrel-ra-2015-4\" data-pitch=\"Psoriasis Treatment www.informationaboutpsoriasis.com Watch a Video About a Moderate to Severe Plaque Psoriasis Treatment.\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><div class=\"spx-ai-desc\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><div class=\"spx-ai-w\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><div class=\"spx-ai-arrow\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(125, 116, 157);\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">Water Helps Your Body Remove Waste</strong></span></div></div></div></div></div><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\">Adequate water intake enables your body to excrete waste through perspiration, urination, and defecation. The kidneys and liver use it to help flush out waste, as do your intestines. Water can also keep you from getting constipated by softening your stools and helping move the food youâ€™ve eaten through your intestinal tract. However, it should be noted that there is no evidence to prove that increasing your fluid intake will cure constipation.</p><div class=\"col-lg-4 col-md-4 col-sm-4 col-xs-12 pull-right clear-right ad-content\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; float: right; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(125, 116, 157);\">&nbsp;<strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">Water Aids in Digestion</strong></span></div><div class=\"col-lg-4 col-md-4 col-sm-4 col-xs-12 pull-right clear-right ad-content\" style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; float: right; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\">Digestion starts with saliva, the basis of which is water. Digestion relies on enzymes that are found in saliva to help break down food and liquid and to dissolve minerals and other nutrients. Proper digestion makes minerals and nutrients more accessible to the body. Water is also necessary to help you digest soluble fiber. With the help of water, this fiber dissolves easily and benefits your bowel health by making well-formed, soft stools that are easy to pass.</div><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(125, 116, 157);\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">Water Prevents You From Becoming Dehydrated</strong></span></p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\">Your body loses fluids when you engage in vigorous exercise, sweat in high heat, or come down with a fever or contract an illness that causes vomiting or diarrhea. If youâ€™re losing fluids for any of these reasons, itâ€™s important to increase your fluid intake so that you can restore your bodyâ€™s natural hydration levels. Your doctor may also recommend that you drink more fluids to help treat other health conditions, like bladder infections and urinary tract stones. If youâ€™re pregnant or nursing, you may want to consult with your physician about your fluid intake because your body will be using more fluids than usual, especially if youâ€™re breastfeeding.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(125, 116, 157);\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">How Much Water Do You Need?</strong></span></p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\">Thereâ€™s no hard and fast rule, and many individuals meet their daily hydration needs by simply drinking water when theyâ€™re thirsty, according to a report on nutrient recommendations from the Institute of Medicine of the National Academies. In fact, most people who are in good physical health get enough fluids by drinking water and other beverages when theyâ€™re thirsty, and also by drinking a beverage with each of their meals, according to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention. If youâ€™re not sure about your hydration level, look at your urine. If itâ€™s clear, youâ€™re in good shape. If itâ€™s dark, youâ€™re probably dehydrated.</p>', 'fea26-04-2021-1619435937.jpg', '', 7, '', '', '', '', '', '2021-04-26 16:48:57'),
(42, 'POST893502', 'eng', 'Toddler', 'What Is A Food Allergy?', 'Text', 'Immediate', '2021-04-26 16:54:00', '#toddler', '#toddler', '<p style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\">A food allergy happens when the body reacts to a product as a harmful substance, causing the bodyâ€™s immune system to release antibodies to fight the â€˜food allergenâ€™ (substance&nbsp;that causes the allergy).&nbsp;As a result&nbsp;the body releases a chemical known as&nbsp;histamine&nbsp;this causes allergic reactions.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(63, 122, 78);\">Symptoms</span></p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(63, 122, 78);\">Of In Sri Lankan Children</span></p><ul style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 30px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\"><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(18, 66, 145);\">Itchy Skin â€“</span></strong>&nbsp;Red itchy bumps, swelling of the face and redness,&nbsp;sudden&nbsp;appearance of&nbsp;eczema, itching and swelling of the lips, tongue or mouth. These are the most common signs of food allergies.</li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(18, 66, 145);\">Swelling â€“</span></strong>&nbsp;Almost immediate swelling of the face, arms or neck.</li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">Severe Abdominal Pain â€“&nbsp;This is caused by a disturbance in the&nbsp;gastrointestinal tract, signs include pain, nausea and&nbsp;loose stools.</li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(18, 66, 145);\">Vomiting â€“</span></strong>&nbsp;Violent vomiting can also be a cause of allergy to food.</li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(18, 66, 145);\">Breathing â€“</span></strong>&nbsp;Runny nose, difficulty in breathing, wheezing, coughing and shortness of breath.</li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(18, 66, 145);\">Fainting â€“</span></strong>&nbsp;Feeling lightheaded and fainting after consuming food causing allergies.</li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(18, 66, 145);\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold;\">Anaphylaxis&nbsp;â€“</strong></span>&nbsp;This is life threatening when the childâ€™s body shows two of the above symptoms with swelling of the&nbsp;air passage&nbsp;causing difficulty in breathing, fainting and even death.</li></ul><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\">Watch out for any of these symptoms if your child feels sick after consuming food. But keep in mind that the above signs do not always mean a food allergy; they can also be caused by bad food. Do not panic unnecessarily but seek immediate medical attention.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(63, 122, 78);\">How Food Allergens Affect The Childs Body</span></p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\">Food allergens cause reactions within different parts of the body such as the:</p><ul style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 30px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\"><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(18, 66, 145);\">Respiratory System</span></strong></li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(18, 66, 145);\">Gastrointestinal Tract</span></strong></li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(18, 66, 145);\">Skin</span></strong></li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(18, 66, 145);\">Cardiovascular System</span></strong></li></ul><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(63, 122, 78);\">Food Causing Allergies</span></p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\">It is wise that parents know the types of food that are more likely to cause an allergic reaction in your child. The following list gives food that is responsible for causing allergies almost 90% of the time:</p><ul style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 30px; padding: 0px; list-style-position: initial; list-style-image: initial; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\"><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(18, 66, 145);\">Milk</span></strong></li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(18, 66, 145);\">Eggs</span></strong></li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(18, 66, 145);\">Peanuts</span></strong></li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(18, 66, 145);\">Soy</span></strong></li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(18, 66, 145);\">Wheat</span></strong></li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(18, 66, 145);\">Fish</span></strong></li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(18, 66, 145);\">Shellfish&nbsp;<span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(63, 122, 78);\">(prawns, crabs etc.)</span></span></strong></li><li style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><strong style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(18, 66, 145);\">Tree Nuts<span style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(63, 122, 78);\">&nbsp;(Cajun, hazelnuts etc â€“&nbsp;<em style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">be mindful of what chocolates you offer the child</em>)</span></span></strong></li></ul><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\">Most of the above are responsible for food allergies in Sri Lankan children. Milk for instance although tolerated can cause an allergy after an illness, this is termed as â€˜lactose intoleranceâ€™ itâ€™s not always permanent. Click&nbsp;Milk &amp; Lactose Intolerance&nbsp;to read more.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\">Certain food colourings in sweets too cause allergic reactions in children while many may develop an allergen to certain foods at a&nbsp;latter&nbsp;stage, most outgrow their food allergies as they reach adulthood.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\">If your child is consuming any of the above food, be mindful and watch out for symptoms. Know when the child is having an allergic reaction and always know what he or she has been eating. In this course, it is wise to advise any day-care or Montessori to make sure your child does not eat food other than what is provided by you.</p><p style=\"border: 0px rgb(229, 229, 229); outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(128, 128, 128); font-family: Raleway; text-align: justify;\">Never&nbsp;over react&nbsp;but always be considerate of what food your child consumes, avoid unnecessary limitations and&nbsp;paranoia, but do be mindful of food allergies.</p>', 'fea26-04-2021-1619436277.jpg', '', 10, '', '', '', '', '', '2021-04-26 16:54:37');
